# Diabetes Risk Assessment Dashboard

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project focuses on analyzing diabetes risk using lifestyle and clinical indicators.  
The analysis was performed using data analytics techniques, with a strong emphasis on data modeling, visualization, and interpretability.

The goal of the project is to identify patterns and high-risk groups associated with diabetic outcomes and to demonstrate the use of Power BI for health-related analytics.

---

## ğŸ§° Tools & Technologies
- Microsoft Power BI
- Power Query
- Microsoft Word & PowerPoint (Documentation & Presentation)

---

## ğŸ“Š Dataset Description
The dataset contains individual-level health and lifestyle attributes, including:
- Glucose levels
- Body Mass Index (BMI)
- Daily calorie intake
- Physical activity levels
- Family history of diabetes
- Diabetes outcome status (Diabetic / Non-Diabetic)

